[{"name":"A Sage's Travel Guide to the North","author":"Zanshareen Sabiyryn","written":"1341 DR","rarity":"uncommon","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Zanshareen Sabiyryn wrote for fellow scholars who must leave their towers and cross the Frontier on foot — notes on safe campsites, reliable map sellers, and which lordlings will demand letters of introduction.\n\nThe guide is dry but precise, with marginal sketches of landmark trees and stone cairns used when snow hides the trail.","tags":["north","travel","geography"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/A_Sage%27s_Travel_Guide_to_the_North"},{"name":"A Brief History of Undermountain","author":"Daizez","written":"1369 DR","rarity":"rare","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Daizez attempts a sober account of Halaster's mad labyrinth beneath Waterdeep — its layers, known entrances, and the expeditions that returned with maps, madness, or neither.\n\nThe author warns that any history of Undermountain is obsolete the moment it is inked, and dedicates a chapter to survivors' contradictory testimony.","tags":["undermountain","history","dungeon"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/A_Brief_History_of_Undermountain"},{"name":"A Harper's Guide","author":"Alustriel","written":"1264 DR","rarity":"rare","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Alustriel of Silverymoon compiled this work long before her elevation — a coded manual on recognizing Zhentarim fronts, safe houses, and the signs that a village song carries more than entertainment.\n\nCopies are rare outside Harper circles; the plain binding disguises a text that has saved more than one agent who memorised its ciphers.","tags":["harpers","history","intrigue"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/A_Harper%27s_Guide"},{"name":"A Wayfarer's Belt-Book of Advice","author":"Rasthiavar of Iriaebor","written":"1282 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Rasthiavar of Iriaebor distilled decades of caravan work into pocket-sized counsel — how to pick guards, when to bribe tollkeepers, and why sleeping in armour saves more lives than any spell.\n\nThe belt-book is literally sized to tuck under a sword belt; margins are crowded with additions in other hands, suggesting it passed through many experienced travellers.","tags":["travel","advice","north"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/A_Wayfarer%27s_Belt-Book_of_Advice"},{"name":"A Historical Treatise of Dragonspear Castle","author":"Unknown","written":"1370 DR","rarity":"uncommon","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"A military historian traces Dragonspear Castle from its founding as a fortified waystation through sieges, abandonment, and its recurring role as a rallying point for devils and cultists.\n\nThe treatise argues that whoever holds the castle controls not a fortress alone but the morale of every caravan crossing the Trade Way.","tags":["dragonspear","history","war"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/A_Historical_Treatise_of_Dragonspear_Castle"},{"name":"A Guide to the Cold North","author":"Alagond, sage of Tashluta","written":"1350 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Alagond of Tashluta wrote for merchants who treat the Frontier as a summer excursion — layering furs, judging ice thickness, and recognising the grey pallor that precedes fatal exposure.\n\nThe guide's appendix on frozen-ground burial rites is copied in nearly every caravan master's chest; southerners who skip it are often the ones found upright in snowdrifts come spring.","tags":["north","geography","nature"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/A_Guide_to_the_Cold_North"},{"name":"A Brief History of the Dessarin","author":"Anonymous scribe of Triboar","written":"1480 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"A frontier chronicle from Triboar traders — river commerce, orc raids through the Stone Bridge gap, and the slow spread of hamlets along the Long Road.\n\nThe author apologises for omitting elven histories prior to human logging, noting that some elders still refuse to speak of the valley's deeper past.","tags":["history","dessarin","trade"],"read_bonus":0},{"name":"A Harper's Companion","author":"Cressaed Wood","written":"1200 DR","rarity":"rare","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Cressaed Wood compiled three volumes of practical counsel for Harper agents — ciphers, cover identities, and the unglamorous work of listening in market squares.\n\nThe third volume is said to list safe houses along the Long Road and the Dessarin; complete sets are kept under lock at Herald's Hall and Silverymoon's High Palace.","tags":["harpers","history","intrigue"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/A_Harper%27s_Companion"},{"name":"A Harper's Song","author":"Alustriel Silverhand","written":"1284 DR","rarity":"rare","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Alustriel Silverhand's lyrical meditation on duty, loss, and the Harper code — part poetry, part memoir, and wholly unsuitable for public performance without training in coded verse.\n\nBards who recite it badly have been known to summon Harper auditors; those who recite it well sometimes receive invitations they cannot refuse.","tags":["harpers","music","philosophy"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/A_Harper%27s_Song"},{"name":"Arglauth's Guide to the North","author":"Arglauth Melroryrr, Sage of Mulmaster","written":"1330 DR","rarity":"uncommon","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Arglauth Melroryrr of Mulmaster wrote for eastern readers who trade with the Frontier but rarely travel it — a sober counterweight to Volo's colour and Elminster's asides.\n\nThe guide emphasises Zhentarim influence, Luskan's naval reach, and the economic choke points where a single burned bridge can starve a city.","tags":["north","geography","trade"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Arglauth%27s_Guide_to_the_North"},{"name":"Architects Arcane: Waterdeep and the Sword Coast North","author":"Paerl Nhesch","written":"1424 DR","rarity":"uncommon","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Paerl Nhesch documents warded foundations, floating spires, and the guild disputes that decide whether a tower may cast shadow on a neighbour's sun-court.\n\nWaterdeep's wards receive three chapters; Neverwinter's rebuilding after spellplague-era fires occupies a cautious appendix marked \"subject to revision.\"","tags":["waterdeep","arcane","architecture"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Architects_Arcane:_Waterdeep_and_the_Sword_Coast_North"},{"name":"Annals of Baldur's Gate","author":"Unknown","written":"before 1492 DR","rarity":"uncommon","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"A civic chronicle tracing Baldur's Gate from flint palisades to walled metropolis — duke successions, guild charters, and the recurring plague of patriar plots.\n\nLater editors appended Flaming Fist campaigns in the Outer City; purists insist the original four volumes end before the Fist became a power in its own right.","tags":["baldurs_gate","history","sword_coast"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Annals_of_Baldur%27s_Gate"},{"name":"A Modest Guide to Sword Coast Wine","author":"Unknown","written":"before 1492 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"A vintner's primer on coastal appellations — where sea salt helps the grape, which Neverwinter cellars age well, and why Amnian exports command prices that have nothing to do with taste.\n\nThe guide's tasting notes are honest to a fault; one Waterdeep merchant sued over the entry on his house blend.","tags":["sword_coast","trade","culture"],"read_bonus":0,"image":"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/forgottenrealms/images/5/56/Red_and_gold_book_bg3.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/394?cb=20231002033431","content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/A_Modest_Guide_to_Sword_Coast_Wine"},{"name":"Aurora's Whole Realms Catalogue","author":"Aurora","written":"mid-14th century DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Aurora's famous mail-order catalogue lists goods from across Faerûn — prices, shipping times, and the occasional item whose description understates its magical properties.\n\nFrontier traders use it as a price index; collectors hunt misprinted editions where Aurora forgot to mention that a \"gentleman's grooming kit\" includes a wand.","tags":["trade","commerce","catalogue"],"read_bonus":0,"image":"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/forgottenrealms/images/e/e2/Auroracover.jpg/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/263?cb=20240229051431","content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Aurora%27s_Whole_Realms_Catalogue"},{"name":"A Merchant's Sagacity","author":"Blackthorn Belgadar","written":"unknown","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"A Merchant's Sagacity — Commercial wisdom dressed as prose — prices, routes, guild customs, and when to walk away from a deal. Blackthorn Belgadar is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to unknown.\n\nFactors along the Long Road keep folded excerpts in strongboxes next to their scales and seals.","tags":["trade","philosophy"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/A_Merchant%27s_Sagacity"},{"name":"A Merchant Master's Life","author":"Asargrym of Baldur's Gate","written":"1327 DR","rarity":"uncommon","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"A Merchant Master's Life — Commercial wisdom dressed as prose — prices, routes, guild customs, and when to walk away from a deal. Asargrym of Baldur's Gate is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 1327 DR.\n\nFactors along the Long Road keep folded excerpts in strongboxes next to their scales and seals.","tags":["baldurs_gate","trade","history"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/A_Merchant_Master%27s_Life"},{"name":"A Ranger's Road","author":"Thaulavvan Tridentstar","written":"unknown","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"A Ranger's Road — Practical notes for wayfarers — tolls, seasons, inns, and the unwritten rules of safe passage. Thaulavvan Tridentstar is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to unknown.\n\nExperienced caravans treat the counsel as suggestion only — but rookies who ignore it seldom return to disagree.","tags":["travel","nature","adventure"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/A_Ranger%27s_Road"},{"name":"Adventurer's Guide","author":"Various","written":"before 1374 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Adventurer's Guide — Practical notes for wayfarers — tolls, seasons, inns, and the unwritten rules of safe passage. Various is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to before 1374 DR.\n\nExperienced caravans treat the counsel as suggestion only — but rookies who ignore it seldom return to disagree.","tags":["adventure","travel"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Adventurer%27s_Guide"},{"name":"A Manyrealms Gallimaufry","author":"Trammeth Anstrelgor","written":"before 1114 DR","rarity":"ancient","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"A Manyrealms Gallimaufry — A regional survey written for travellers who cannot afford to learn geography from dead companions. Trammeth Anstrelgor is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to before 1114 DR.\n\nMaps are absent or obsolete in most copies; readers are expected to update the text with their own ink.","tags":["geography","history","faerun"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/A_Manyrealms_Gallimaufry"},{"name":"A Myth Drannan Amphigory","author":"Elminster","written":"1337 DR","rarity":"rare","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"A Myth Drannan Amphigory — A chronicle preserved in northern and coastal scriptoria — dates, names, and the sort of detail merchants pretend not to need. Elminster is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 1337 DR.\n\nLater hands added marginal dates and crossed out names; historians still argue which revisions were propaganda.","tags":["history","elves","myth"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/A_Myth_Drannan_Amphigory"},{"name":"Arrr, Yarrr, and Garrr: A Guide to the Pirate Idiom","author":"Unknown","written":"before 1372 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Arrr, Yarrr, and Garrr: A Guide to the Pirate Idiom — An in-universe work listed in Candlekeep indices and frontier libraries throughout the Heartlands. Library catalogues list no certain author; the work is dated to before 1372 DR.\n\nCopies vary by scriptorium; Candlekeep treats the title as known though completeness is never guaranteed.","tags":["sea","culture","humor"],"read_bonus":0,"image":"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/forgottenrealms/images/3/32/Nwn_pirate_book.png/revision/latest?cb=20241119082017","content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Arrr,_Yarrr,_and_Garrr%3A_A_Guide_to_the_Pirate_Idiom"},{"name":"Alias Versus the Night Masks","author":"Jamal the Thespian","written":"1370 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"Alias Versus the Night Masks — A popular tale in print — performed in taverns before it was ever bound between covers. Jamal the Thespian is credited in library catalogues; the work is dated to 1370 DR.\n\nCritics call it low art; innkeepers call it excellent for business on rainy nights.","tags":["fiction","adventure","intrigue"],"read_bonus":0,"content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/Alias_Versus_the_Night_Masks"},{"name":"A Traveler's Guide to Baldur's Gate","author":"Unknown","written":"before 1492 DR","rarity":"common","language":"Common","type":"original","description":"A Traveler's Guide to Baldur's Gate — Practical notes for wayfarers — tolls, seasons, inns, and the unwritten rules of safe passage. Library catalogues list no certain author; the work is dated to before 1492 DR.\n\nExperienced caravans treat the counsel as suggestion only — but rookies who ignore it seldom return to disagree.","tags":["baldurs_gate","travel","geography"],"read_bonus":0,"image":"https://static.wikia.nocookie.net/forgottenrealms/images/7/76/BG3_green_book.png/revision/latest/scale-to-width-down/353?cb=20220223160036","content_link":"https://forgottenrealms.fandom.com/wiki/A_Traveler%27s_Guide_to_Baldur%27s_Gate"}]